 succeeded in 0ms:
   296	- **`CLAUDE.md`** — symlink to `AGENTS.md`.
   297	
   298	### G. Build & CI config
   299	
   300	**Bootstrap is docs-only**, so CI runs exactly one check.
   301	
   302	- `.github/workflows/ci.yml` — single workflow named `ci`, single job
   303	  named **`docs-lint`**. That job name is also the required status
   304	  check in branch protection (pinned explicitly so the `gh api` call
   305	  is deterministic).
   306	- The `docs-lint` job:
   307	  1. Checks out.
   308	  2. Runs exactly this command (same in CI and local verification):
   309	
   310	     ```bash
   311	     markdownlint-cli2 "**/*.md" "#node_modules" "#.venv" "#docs/archive/**"
   312	     ```
   313	
   314	     Configuration comes from the repo's `.markdownlint.json`. The
   315	     `docs/archive/**` exclusion is deliberate: archived historical
   316	     documents (moved, not rewritten) should not be held to the new
   317	     lint rules — that would be busywork against the archive's
   318	     purpose. The `#node_modules` and `#.venv` exclusions guard
   319	     against noise from future dependency installs.
   320	  3. Exits 0 if all markdown passes.
   321	- **No Python job** at bootstrap (no Python files exist).
   322	- **No JSON Schema job** at bootstrap (no schemas exist, and an
   323	  empty-glob job is brittle — either a find returning nothing exits 0
   324	  quietly and hides a real misconfiguration, or the tool errors on
   325	  no-input. Easier to add this job in Phase 1 when the first schema
   326	  lands.)
   327	- **Later phases add jobs**, each as a distinct job name (so branch
   328	  protection can require each one as it stabilizes):
   329	  - Phase 1: `schema-validity` — validates `spec/v0/schemas/*.schema.json`.
   330	  - Phase 3: `python-lint` (ruff), `python-typecheck` (pyright),
   331	    `python-test` (pytest) — once the first package exists and has a
   332	    real test.
   333	  - Phase 3+: `schema-parity` — Pydantic models match their JSON
   334	    Schemas.
   335	  - Phase 11: `conformance` — runs the conformance suite against
   336	    the reference impl.
   337	
   338	### H. Git + GitHub execution
   339	
   340	Same as before:
   341	
   342	1. `git init -b main`
   343	2. Initial commit containing all of the above.
   344	3. `gh auth status`.
   345	4. `gh repo create eden --private --source . --remote origin --push \
   346	   --description "A protocol for directed code evolution orchestration"`.
   347	5. `gh repo edit --add-topic protocol --add-topic specification \
   348	   --add-topic directed-evolution --add-topic orchestration \
   349	   --add-topic ai --add-topic research-automation`.
   350	6. Wait for the first `docs-lint` run on `main` to complete (so the
   351	   check name is registered in GitHub's status-check cache), **then**
   352	   enable branch protection.
   353	7. Branch protection uses **classic branch protection** (not the
   354	   newer repository rulesets — classic is better-documented for
   355	   scripted setup and the two tools can coexist). Call:
   356	
   357	   ```bash
   358	   gh api -X PUT "repos/<user>/eden/branches/main/protection" \
   359	     -H "Accept: application/vnd.github+json" \
   360	     --input - <<'JSON'
   361	   {
   362	     "required_status_checks": {
   363	       "strict": true,
   364	       "contexts": ["docs-lint"]
   365	     },
   366	     "enforce_admins": false,
   367	     "required_pull_request_reviews": {
   368	       "required_approving_review_count": 0,
   369	       "dismiss_stale_reviews": false,
   370	       "require_code_owner_reviews": false
   371	     },
   372	     "restrictions": null,
   373	     "allow_force_pushes": false,
   374	     "allow_deletions": false
   375	   }
   376	   JSON
   377	   ```
   378	
   379	   Rationale for each field:
   380	   - `contexts: ["docs-lint"]` — exact CI job name pinned in section G.
   381	     Added to as Phase 3 / Phase 11 introduce more jobs.
   382	   - `enforce_admins: false` — solo-repo hotfix path stays open.
   383	   - `required_approving_review_count: 0` — solo contributor;
   384	     bumping this to 1+ would block every merge. Increase when
   385	     collaborators arrive.
   386	   - `strict: true` — branches must be up-to-date with `main` before
   387	     merging; cheap safety on a low-traffic repo.
   388	   - `allow_force_pushes: false`, `allow_deletions: false` — keep
   389	     `main` durable.
   390	
